## Common Tasks

### First-time deployment
```bash
# Bootstrap CDK (once per account/region)
cd tools/aws-cdk && npx cdk bootstrap

# Deploy all stacks
pnpm cdk:deploy
```

### Deploy frontend
```bash
nx run client:build
aws s3 sync dist/apps/client s3://my-saas-frontend-301394200094-us-east-1 --delete
aws cloudfront create-invalidation --distribution-id E2UT0W7O4SW87G --paths "/*"
```

### Build & push API Docker image
```bash
aws ecr get-login-password --region us-east-1 | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin 301394200094.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com
docker build --platform linux/amd64 -t my-saas-api:latest .
docker tag my-saas-api:latest 301394200094.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/my-saas-api:latest
docker push 301394200094.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/my-saas-api:latest
# Force ECS to redeploy with new image:
aws ecs update-service --cluster my-saas-cluster --service my-saas-api --force-new-deployment
```

## Secrets Management

Two secrets in AWS Secrets Manager:
- `my-saas/database-credentials` — auto-generated by RDS (username, password)
- `my-saas/app-secrets` — application config, **must be manually populated after first deploy**

### Required app secrets (server won't start without these)

The app validates all config on startup via Zod (`apps/server/src/config/schema.ts`). Empty strings on `.url()` fields crash the container → ECS circuit breaker → `ROLLBACK_COMPLETE`.

| Key | Notes |
|-----|-------|
| `DATABASE_URL` | `postgresql://postgres:<pass>@<rds-endpoint>:5432/mysaas` |
| `ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET` | `openssl rand -hex 32` |
| `REFRESH_TOKEN_SECRET` | `openssl rand -hex 32` |
| `PUBLIC_URL` | ALB DNS — `http://my-saas-alb-445995649.us-east-1.elb.amazonaws.com` |
| `STORAGE_URL` | `https://my-saas-uploads-301394200094-us-east-1.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com` |
| `STORAGE_ENDPOINT` | `s3.amazonaws.com` |
| `STORAGE_PORT` | `443` |
| `STORAGE_BUCKET` | `my-saas-uploads-301394200094-us-east-1` |
| `STORAGE_ACCESS_KEY` | IAM user `my-saas-s3-user` access key |
| `STORAGE_SECRET_KEY` | IAM user `my-saas-s3-user` secret key |
| `STORAGE_USE_SSL` | `true` |
| `MAIL_FROM` | `noreply@example.com` (placeholder) |
| `SMTP_URL` | `smtp://localhost:25` (placeholder) |
| Optional URL fields | Set to `http://placeholder.example.com` — empty string fails Zod `.url()` |

### Storage IAM (important)

MinIO SDK requires **explicit credentials** — it does NOT use the ECS task role. Create a dedicated IAM user:

```bash
aws iam create-user --user-name my-saas-s3-user
aws iam put-user-policy --user-name my-saas-s3-user --policy-name s3-access --policy-document '{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [{"Effect": "Allow", "Action": ["s3:GetObject","s3:PutObject","s3:DeleteObject","s3:ListBucket","s3:GetBucketLocation"],
    "Resource": ["arn:aws:s3:::my-saas-uploads-301394200094-us-east-1","arn:aws:s3:::my-saas-uploads-301394200094-us-east-1/*"]}]}'
aws iam create-access-key --user-name my-saas-s3-user
```

## Troubleshooting

### Stack in ROLLBACK_COMPLETE — must delete before redeploying

```bash
aws cloudformation delete-stack --stack-name MySaasApiStack
aws cloudformation wait stack-delete-complete --stack-name MySaasApiStack
# Also clear orphaned log groups (block redeployment otherwise)
aws logs delete-log-group --log-group-name /ecs/my-saas-api
aws logs delete-log-group --log-group-name /ecs/my-saas-adminer
cd tools/aws-cdk && npx cdk deploy MySaasApiStack --require-approval never
```

### ECS circuit breaker triggered — debug steps

```bash
# 1. Find failure reason
aws cloudformation describe-stack-events --stack-name MySaasApiStack \
  --query 'StackEvents[?ResourceStatus==`CREATE_FAILED`].[LogicalResourceId,ResourceStatusReason]' --output table

# 2. Check container logs
aws logs get-log-events --log-group-name /ecs/my-saas-api \
  --log-stream-name $(aws logs describe-log-streams --log-group-name /ecs/my-saas-api \
    --order-by LastEventTime --descending --query 'logStreams[0].logStreamName' --output text) \
  --limit 50 --query 'events[*].message' --output text
```

### Audit which secrets are set vs empty
```bash
aws secretsmanager get-secret-value --secret-id my-saas/app-secrets \
  --query SecretString --output text | tr -d '\n' | \
  python3 -c "import sys,json; d=json.loads(sys.stdin.read()); print('\n'.join(f'{k}: {\"SET\" if v.strip() else \"EMPTY\"}' for k,v in d.items() if isinstance(v,str)))"
```
